cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on improving the use of vector-space word embeddings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses machine learning techniques for learning these embeddings, which suggests that it could also fit into cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses non-parametric estimation, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses word similarity and context, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses scalability, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
